Atlas AI – Fagron Physician Prescription Module

Objective

Create a simplified physician-facing prescription workflow inside Atlas AI for doctors referred by Fagron Genomics.

The primary goal is to allow physicians to upload a PDF prescription or treatment recommendation generated from Fagron Genomics, automatically extract all relevant data using OCR and AI, and convert it into a structured Atlas AI Prescription with minimal user interaction.

The design must maximize reuse of the existing Prescription Module and existing Patient infrastructure, avoiding duplicate logic whenever possible.

⸻

User Access Logic

When a user logs in:

IF:

* User Role = Physician
* Referral Source = Fagron Genomics

THEN:

Display the “Fagron Physician Workspace” instead of the standard Atlas Prescription Workflow.

This workspace should be intentionally simplified and optimized for speed.

⸻

Main Workflow

Step 1 – Upload Prescription PDF

Primary CTA:

“Upload Fagron Recommendation”

Accepted formats:

* PDF
* Image (JPG, PNG)
* Multi-page PDF

Drag & Drop supported.

⸻

Step 2 – OCR + AI Extraction

After upload:

Use OCR to extract all visible text.

Then use AI to identify:

Patient Information

* Patient Name
* Patient ID
* Date of Birth
* Gender
* Contact Information (if available)

Prescription Information

* Product Name
* Active Ingredients
* Strength
* Dosage
* Quantity
* Administration Route
* Frequency
* Duration
* Refills (if specified)

Clinical Information

* Biomarkers referenced
* Genetic markers referenced
* Clinical notes
* Physician comments

⸻

Step 3 – Prescription Conversion

Automatically convert extracted data into the existing Atlas Prescription structure.

Important:

DO NOT create a new prescription engine.

Reuse:

* Existing Prescription Entity
* Existing Prescription Statuses
* Existing Prescription Database
* Existing Prescription Validation Logic
* Existing Pricing Engine
* Existing Refill Logic

The uploaded PDF becomes simply another Prescription Creation Method.

Existing methods:

* Manual Prescription
* Biomarker-driven Prescription
* Protocol-driven Prescription

Add:

* PDF OCR Prescription

⸻

