UX Requirements

The physician should be able to:

1. Login
2. Upload PDF
3. Review extracted data
4. Save

In under 60 seconds.

No complex prescription builder.

No protocol configuration.

No catalog management.

No inventory management.

Hide all non-essential functionality.

⸻

Permissions

Physician can:

* Upload prescriptions
* View own patients
* View prescription history
* View refill reminders
* Request quotation

Physician cannot:

* Edit product catalog
* Edit protocols
* Edit pricing rules
* Manage suppliers
* Manage inventory

⸻

Quotation Integration

Each prescription should include a simple:

“Request Quote”

button.

When pressed:

Reuse the existing Atlas quotation engine.

No duplicate quotation workflow should be created.

⸻

Technical Architecture

Principle:

Reuse before building.

Reuse:

* Patient Module
* Prescription Module
* Calendar Module
* Notifications Module
* Quotation Module
* User Management Module

Create only:

* Fagron Physician Workspace
* PDF OCR Service
* Prescription Mapping Layer

Everything else must leverage existing Atlas AI infrastructure.

⸻

Success Metric

A Fagron physician should be able to convert a PDF recommendation into a complete Atlas prescription, stored in the patient record and scheduled for refill follow-up, in less than one minute with fewer than three clicks.
